First Lady Michelle Obama will be hosting the Broadway cast of Hamilton at the White House on March 14th. The event will include a student workshop, student Q&A, and a performance of musical selections from Hamilton. Hamilton is a musical that tells the story of Alexander Hamilton, one of America's Founding Fathers. The musical's score combines various genres such as hip-hop, jazz, blues, rap, R&B, and Broadway. The musical is based on Ron Chernow's biography of Alexander Hamilton. This event follows a previous performance by Lin-Manuel Miranda, the creator of Hamilton, at a poetry and music event hosted by the President and First Lady in 2009.